The paper discusses functional verification of array-intensive programs, which involves analyzing the correctness of program transformations. This topic is closely related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE), as well as computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed computing (cs.DC) since array-intensive programs can be parallelized across multiple machines. Additionally, the paper may also touch on logic (cs.LO) since functional verification involves reasoning about program correctness.
